  <para>This article shows various examples of inserting images into a document. The first is an image that is placed directly inside the &lt;article/&gt; element.</para>

  <mediaobject>
	<alt>The DocBook: TDG Duck</alt>
    <imageobject>
      <imagedata
		  format="JPG"
    	  fileref="docbook-largecover.jpg"/>
	</imageobject>
  </mediaobject>

  <para>This is an image (<mediaobject>
	<alt>The DocBook: TDG Duck</alt>
    <imageobject>
      <imagedata
		  width="1.322cm"
		  height="1.734464cm"
		  format="JPG"
    	  fileref="docbook-largecover.jpg"/>
	</imageobject>
  </mediaobject>) inside a paragraph.</para>

  <para>This is an image (<mediaobject>
    <imageobject>
      <imagedata
		  height="0.4cm"
		  format="JPG"
    	  fileref="docbook-largecover.jpg"/>
	</imageobject>
  </mediaobject>) only has the height defined while this one (<mediaobject>
    <imageobject>
      <imagedata
		  width="0.4cm"
		  format="JPG"
    	  fileref="docbook-largecover.jpg"/>
	</imageobject>
  </mediaobject>) only has the width defined.</para>

